Here's what I want to know--

00:39:26,180 --> 00:39:29,851
you burned through $400,000
of your own money

00:39:29,917 --> 00:39:31,686
in a few years.

00:39:31,753 --> 00:39:33,888
For you not to burn through
$300,000

00:39:33,955 --> 00:39:36,291
of my and Daymond's money,

00:39:36,357 --> 00:39:38,092
I gotta have more control.

00:39:38,159 --> 00:39:41,029
So how much more than 50%

00:39:41,095 --> 00:39:43,631
are you willing to give me?

00:39:43,698 --> 00:39:44,699
Um...

00:39:44,766 --> 00:39:47,135
we would be willing
to give you

00:39:47,201 --> 00:39:48,136
um...

00:39:48,202 --> 00:39:49,437
take a breath.
Um... (laughs)

00:39:49,504 --> 00:39:50,438
Take a breath.
Thank you.

00:39:50,505 --> 00:39:51,873
Slow down.

00:39:51,939 --> 00:39:55,009
(both whisper indistinctly)

00:39:55,076 --> 00:39:56,944
So we would give you

00:39:57,011 --> 00:39:59,414
a greater...
number.

00:39:59,480 --> 00:40:00,415
Percentage of equity...
55%.

00:40:00,481 --> 00:40:01,549
Than we have.

00:40:01,616 --> 00:40:03,751
Not enough for me.
I'm out again.

00:40:03,818 --> 00:40:06,854
Not enough?

00:40:06,921 --> 00:40:08,456
All right. Hold on, Robert.
Robert...

00:40:08,523 --> 00:40:10,024
they came in.

00:40:10,091 --> 00:40:12,293
They went from 15% to 38%

00:40:12,360 --> 00:40:14,696
to 50% to 55%.

00:40:14,762 --> 00:40:16,831
I-I have to respect that
in some sense.

00:40:16,898 --> 00:40:18,967
Would you just still come in
if I do 55%?

00:40:19,033 --> 00:40:21,803
'Cause I can't do it
without you.

00:40:21,869 --> 00:40:25,139
♪♪

00:40:25,206 --> 00:40:28,076
Can't do it.

00:40:28,142 --> 00:40:30,211
They're--They're...

00:40:30,278 --> 00:40:31,746
they're just--

00:40:31,813 --> 00:40:33,648
There are so many issues--

00:40:33,715 --> 00:40:34,816
the EUROPE--
No, it--
No, it's a challenge.

00:40:34,882 --> 00:40:35,817
I know. I know.
I hear what you're saying.

00:40:35,883 --> 00:40:37,619
Robert, Robert,
are you in at 65%?

00:40:37,685 --> 00:40:38,786
Are you in at 65%?

00:40:38,853 --> 00:40:40,154
Can you help us take this

00:40:40,221 --> 00:40:42,123
where we need to go
with this thing?

00:40:42,190 --> 00:40:45,960
You and daymond together,
take this thing at 65%?

00:40:49,464 --> 00:40:50,698
(Arlene) You love the product.
I mean--

00:40:50,765 --> 00:40:52,133
I love the PRODUCT,
Arlene,

00:40:52,200 --> 00:40:54,035
and that is the only reason
I'm still talking to you.

00:40:54,102 --> 00:40:55,403
But my challenge is...

00:40:55,470 --> 00:40:56,904
(desirée)
and we're listening to you.

00:40:56,971 --> 00:40:58,473
Every time you get asked
a business question,

00:40:58,539 --> 00:41:01,275
I hear dreams, I hear hopes,
I hear future.

00:41:01,342 --> 00:41:02,644
It's great.
(Arlene)
Like every entrepreneur.

00:41:02,710 --> 00:41:04,812
But I gotta hear Business.
That's my Concern.

00:41:04,879 --> 00:41:05,813
That's why they need us,
Rob.

00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:07,115
That's why
we need you.

00:41:07,181 --> 00:41:08,916
We burned through
that $400,00,

00:41:08,983 --> 00:41:11,019
and I take responsibility
to that,

00:41:11,085 --> 00:41:12,353
because I had a big dream

00:41:12,420 --> 00:41:14,889
that we could do this
where we have

00:41:14,956 --> 00:41:17,358
distributors interested
in us in Italy...

00:41:17,425 --> 00:41:18,359
All right.
In Europe.

00:41:18,426 --> 00:41:19,360
Okay, but--
(Robert) Arlene.

00:41:19,427 --> 00:41:20,662
Yeah?
The--the--

00:41:20,728 --> 00:41:22,196
my bad. My bad, Robert.
(daymond)
Arlene, just--

00:41:22,263 --> 00:41:24,165
Come on. Come back
to the table, baby!

00:41:24,232 --> 00:41:26,000
But there you are again!
There you are again!
(laughs)

00:41:26,067 --> 00:41:27,869
(daymond) rob, this--
400 grand. "My bad."

00:41:27,935 --> 00:41:29,570
I just pissed it away, right?
Yeah. No. I didn't do that.

00:41:29,637 --> 00:41:31,706
Hey, you know what, Arlene?

00:41:31,773 --> 00:41:34,342
$400,000 was a lot of money
to me when I didn't have any.

00:41:34,409 --> 00:41:36,010
It's still a lot of money!
It's still
a lot of money to me.

00:41:36,077 --> 00:41:37,578
It's still a lot
of money.

00:41:37,645 --> 00:41:38,746
I can't do it 'cause you're
throwing that money away.

00:41:38,813 --> 00:41:41,115
If daymond wants to throw
his money away,

00:41:41,182 --> 00:41:42,116
I'm gonna let him do it.

00:41:42,183 --> 00:41:43,418
I'm out.

00:41:43,484 --> 00:41:44,852
Ugh.
Ohh.

00:41:44,919 --> 00:41:45,853
We--

00:41:45,920 --> 00:41:47,088
We were willing to,

00:41:47,155 --> 00:41:50,391
you know,
refocus our business.

00:41:50,458 --> 00:41:52,427
We are willing to--
to grow our business.

00:41:52,493 --> 00:41:54,729
We actually have
a marketing plan for the U.S.

00:41:54,796 --> 00:41:55,897
(daymond) guys, listen.

00:41:57,131 --> 00:41:59,267
Robert's out.

00:42:01,135 --> 00:42:03,504
But I got good news
for you. I'm in.

00:42:03,571 --> 00:42:04,806
Whoo!
Aah!

00:42:04,872 --> 00:42:06,741
I can't believe it.
Damn.

00:42:06,808 --> 00:42:07,976
Thank you!
Oh, my goodness!

00:42:08,042 --> 00:42:10,311
All right, so now
I'm betting on you guys.

00:42:10,378 --> 00:42:11,546
Don't make me look bad.

00:42:11,612 --> 00:42:12,647
We won't.
Not a chance.

00:42:12,714 --> 00:42:13,648
All right.
We won't.

00:42:13,715 --> 00:42:15,116
Thank you.
Thank you, sharks!

00:42:15,183 --> 00:42:16,250
(mark)
Congratulations, ladies.

00:42:16,317 --> 00:42:17,518
(laughing)

00:42:17,585 --> 00:42:18,753
(Arlene) God!

00:42:18,820 --> 00:42:19,921
(Barbara) You're my hero.

00:42:19,988 --> 00:42:21,489
Whoo-Hoo!
Oh, god.

00:42:21,556 --> 00:42:23,157
(laughing) We got it.

00:42:23,224 --> 00:42:25,159
I'm glad we had
our protective armor on,

00:42:25,226 --> 00:42:27,562
because we sure took
a beating out there,

00:42:27,629 --> 00:42:29,464
